=encoding utf-8

=head1 USAGE

    dsync_cpsrvd_client_whm [--help]

    dsync_cpsrvd_client_whm <hostname> <authn_user> <api_token> <email_account>

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This command connects a calling L<dsync(1)> process with a dsync server through
a cpsrvd proxy.

You’ll probably use this command as an argument to L<dsync(1)> rather than
calling it directly. For example, to merge C<hal@example.com>’s mail from
C<remote.example.com> to the local server, do:

    dsync -D -u hal@example.com backup -R -1 /usr/local/cpanel/bin/dsync_cpsrvd_client remote.example.com root F43ADD98E9AB17558FCC hal@example.com

… or, for a system account C<nick>:

    dsync -D -u nick backup -R -1 /usr/local/cpanel/bin/dsync_cpsrvd_client remote.example.com root F43ADD98E9AB17558FCC _mainaccount@example.com

=head1 SEE ALSO

F<bin/dsync_cpsrvd_client_cpanel> for authenticating via cPanel rather than
WHM.

